To determine the total amount of material Jo needs to make 20 small and 8 large masks, we can follow these steps:

1. Calculate the material needed for the small masks:
   - Jo needs 2 yards of material for 4 small masks, so for 20 small masks, she would need:
   \begin{align}
   \frac{2\text{ yards}}{4\text{ masks}}\times 20\ \text{masks} &= 10\text{ yards}
   \end{align}

2. Calculate the material needed for the large masks:
   - Jo needs 2.25 yards of material for 3 large masks, so for 8 large masks, she would need:
   \begin{align}
   \frac{2.25\text{ yards}}{3\text{ masks}}\times 8\ \text{masks} &= 6.0\text{ (or }18/3\text{)}\text{ yards}
   \end{align}

3. To find the total material needed, add the material for small and large masks together:
   \begin{align}
   &\hspace{-1cm}\text{Total material} = 10\text{ yards (small)} + 6\text{ yards (large)}\\
   &=16\text{ yards}
   \end{align}

Therefore, Jo would need 16 yards of material to make 20 small and 8 large masks.
